				\begin{document}$$\Delta \frac{{{\text{F}}_{{\text{v}}} }}{{{\text{F}}_{{\text{m}}} }}{ = }\frac{{\left( {{\text{F}}_{{\text{v}}} {\text{/F}}_{{\text{m}}} } \right)_{{{\text{after}}\;{\text{treatment}}}} }}{{\left( {{\text{F}}_{{\text{v}}} {\text{/F}}_{{\text{m}}} } \right)_{{{\text{before}}\;{\text{treatment}}}} }}$$\end{document}ΔFvFm=Fv/FmaftertreatmentFv/FmbeforetreatmentThis ratio was used to evaluate the physiological condition of macroalgae, where values > 1 indicate an increase in the Fv/Fm, i.e. improved performance, and values < 1 indicate a decrease in Fv/Fm, i.e. poorer performance after the treatments. The variation in weight (ΔWeight) indicated the potential for desiccative water loss under emersion in the field, which is linked to the different physiological responses of each species under desiccation stress. ΔWeight was calculated in the same way as ΔFv/Fm.
